  "prompt": "PAN Card: I lost my Aadhaar card. How can I get a second copy?",
  "response": "To get a duplicate Aadhaar card, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. Online Method:\n- Visit UIDAI website (https://uidai.gov.in/)\n- Click on \"Retrieve Lost/Forgotten EID/UID\"\n- Enter your Aadhaar number or Virtual ID\n- Verify through OTP\n- Download or print your Aadhaar card\n\n2. Offline Method:\n- Visit nearest Aadhaar Seva Kendra\n- Fill out Aadhaar Reprint/Update form\n- Carry original documents for identification\n- Pay a small fee (around \u20b950)\n\n3. By Postal Service:\n- Download Aadhaar reprint form from UIDAI website\n- Fill out the form\n- Send it to UIDAI Regional Office with required documents\n\n4. Helpline/Support:\n- Call UIDAI Helpline: 1947\n- Email: help@uidai.gov.in\n\nRequired Documents:\n- Proof of identity\n- Proof of address\n- Recent photograph\n\nNote: Keep your Aadhaar number handy during the process. The entire process typically takes 5-7 working days.",
